Use emitted discovery fields to build **candidate relationships**.

Then run validation rules to produce **true attack edges**.

```text
Raw relationship:
ALB → TargetGroup

Validated attack edge:
ALB → CAN_REACH → EC2
only if listener + target healthy + SG/network allows
```

So yes, you need:

```text
network reachability validation
IAM permission validation
data access validation
identity assumption validation
```

For v1, start with only two validators:

```text
1. Internet reachability validator
2. IAM permission validator
```

That will give you meaningful attack paths.




